I had Prof. Grinnell for MATA23(Linear Algebgra), MATA33, and MATA32 and he was the best math prof I ever had. I strongly recommend going to his lectures, paying attention, and provoke your learning experience by asking questions. Go to his office hours, he is more than happy to help.  His exams are only difficult if you don't prepare for it.

If you take the course with him, be sure to dedicate long hours and understand the material thoroughly. He's super smart and very approachable. Speaking to him privately is the best because he's a really nice guy and super sweet. To do well in his class, make sure to do all the assignments and past tests. His evaluations are super hard!
Very nice and really care about students. The classroom is always packed, students need to arrive in advanced to secure a seat in the front.

This course is the death of management students so good luck applying!
